# Test Runner Port Guard

Before running any Playwright or Vitest command, always terminate any process listening on port `3000`.

Use PowerShell:

```powershell
$pids = Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -ExpandProperty OwningProcess -Unique
if ($pids) { $pids | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_ -Force } }
```

Then run the requested Playwright/Vitest command.

Applies to:
- `npm run test:ui`
- `npm run test:browser`
- `npm run test`
- `npx playwright test ...`
- `vitest ...`
